[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rio Olympics 2016: Times for BBC TV, radio and online coverage

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The BBC will bring you live coverage of every gold medal at Rio 2016 across TV, radio and digital platforms.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
BBC TV will broadcast more than 3,000 hours of coverage, including 550 hours on BBC One and BBC Four, while Radio 5 live will have extensive live coverage.
Up to 24 live video streams will show every moment from 42 sports and 17 days of action online.
Fans will also be able to sign up for medal alerts and follow their favourite sport on the BBC Sport website and app.
Coverage starts with the opening ceremony on 5 August, with live action from around 13:00 BST until 04:00 every day until the closing ceremony on 21 August.
You can catch up with all the overnight action with BBC One Breakfast and Radio 5 live Olympic Breakfast before BBC Two replays the previous night's coverage in full.
The Olympics Playlist, a catch-up programme will also be available to view every morning on BBC iPlayer.
All the live action as well as full replays and on-demand highlights will also be available on mobile, desktop, connected TVs and BBC Sport app, while in-play video highlights will be included in the daily live text commentary. Live streams will also be accessible via the iPlayer website.
Satellite, Cable and Freeview* viewers will have an extra seven Red Button streams to choose from all day, plus an eighth from 19:00-05.30 BST.
Note: where both SD and HD versions are carried, Sky and Freesat make the HD versions available on the lower EPG numbers.
*Freeview SD viewers and those in some rural areas will receive one stream on channel 600 from 19:00-05.30 and a second stream on 601 from 21:00-05.30. Click here for more information.
Viewers with access to Red Button+ via connected TVs or platforms like Virgin TiVo will be able to access up to 24 live streams.
Event start times are subject to change and the BBC is not responsible for any that may be made. Also, coverage can be subject to late schedule changes, so details may differ from this page.
